I'm fine, really.
I'm sorry.

724
01:08:05,617 --> 01:08:09,053
It was my fault. I should've watched
where I was going.

725
01:08:09,121 --> 01:08:11,146
No, I shouldn't
have had it there.

726
01:08:11,223 --> 01:08:14,386
The way my day's going,
I'm lucky you didn't trip and sue me.

727
01:08:14,459 --> 01:08:17,895
What do you got in there ?
Plumbing supplies ?

728
01:08:17,963 --> 01:08:22,332
Look, this is gonna sound crazy,
but I have a little problem...

729
01:08:22,401 --> 01:08:25,063
and I was wondering
if you could help me out.

730
01:08:25,137 --> 01:08:27,867
You see that little boy
sitting over there ?

731
01:08:27,939 --> 01:08:31,136
Do you think you could watch him
for a couple of minutes ?

732
01:08:31,209 --> 01:08:35,373
You didn't just accidentally
trip over the case, did you ?

733
01:08:35,447 --> 01:08:40,111
He's autistic.
And I'm his Big Brother.

734
01:08:40,185 --> 01:08:44,212
Not his real big brother, you know ?
Big Brothers of America.

735
01:08:44,289 --> 01:08:47,725
It's going really well, but I need
to get a prescription filled for him.

736
01:08:47,793 --> 01:08:52,594
Normally I'd take him with me,
but I don't like to disturb him
when he's sitting so calmly.

737
01:08:52,664 --> 01:08:56,031
You don't have to do anything.
Just sit here and be your lovely self.

738
01:08:56,101 --> 01:08:58,092
Please.

739
01:08:58,170 --> 01:09:02,072
- Okay, yeah. What's his name ?
- Simon.

740
01:09:02,140 --> 01:09:04,165
- You sure this is okay ?
- Y eah.

741
01:09:04,242 --> 01:09:07,541
If I can handle a district manager,
I can handle anyone.

742
01:09:07,612 --> 01:09:11,412
Thank you. I will be right back.
Oh !

743
01:09:11,483 --> 01:09:13,644
- What's your name ?
- Stacey.

744
01:09:13,719 --> 01:09:16,620
- Stacey--
- Sebring.

745
01:09:16,688 --> 01:09:20,283
Stacey, thank you so much.
I'll be right back. I promise.

746
01:09:24,129 --> 01:09:27,189
Would have done it
without the flattery ?

747
01:09:33,305 --> 01:09:35,273
Hey, Simon.

748
01:09:35,340 --> 01:09:37,774
# # [ Reggae ]

749
01:09:49,988 --> 01:09:52,252
Just keep walking.
Keep walking.

750
01:09:52,324 --> 01:09:54,815
- Jeffries ?
- Just keep walking.

751
01:09:54,893 --> 01:09:57,191
I wasn't sure
you'd be here.

752
01:09:57,262 --> 01:10:01,426
Simon's read the code twice. That's
really incredible. Also very dangerous.

753
01:10:01,500 --> 01:10:04,594
- Who do you work for ? The C.l.A. ?
- No.

754
01:10:04,669 --> 01:10:08,002
- The Defense Department ?
- I'm afraid you're not that lucky.

755
01:10:08,073 --> 01:10:11,236
I think the F.B.l. likes to call us
"No Such Agency."

756
01:10:11,309 --> 01:10:15,507
- Why does the N.S.A. want
a 9-year-old autistic boy ?
- The brain is still a mystery.

757
01:10:15,580 --> 01:10:17,104
What ?

758
01:10:17,182 --> 01:10:19,446
The Reagan administration mandated
the National Security Agency...

759
01:10:19,518 --> 01:10:22,976
to generate a new code
to protect American informants
working for foreign governments.

760
01:10:23,054 --> 01:10:26,285
We developed a super code
at huge expense.

761
01:10:26,358 --> 01:10:30,658
Named it Mercury.
We thought it was impenetrable.

762
01:10:30,729 --> 01:10:33,357
You're telling me a kid cracked
a government super code ?

763
01:10:33,432 --> 01:10:36,128
It doesn't matter.
He can read it.

764
01:10:36,201 --> 01:10:39,637
He might even be able to recreate it.
That's why his life is in danger.

765
01:10:39,704 --> 01:10:44,266
- N.S.A. is willing to have this
boy killed to protect a code ?
- We may have already tried.

766
01:10:44,342 --> 01:10:48,301
I think my division chief
may have given orders--

767
01:10:48,380 --> 01:10:51,747
I'm a cryptographer, a nerd.
I don't know what these people do.

768
01:10:51,817 --> 01:10:54,547
Maybe it's routine killing kids,
or maybe my boss is an aberration.

769
01:10:54,619 --> 01:10:56,553
[ Gunshot ]

770
01:10:56,621 --> 01:10:59,647
[ Crowd Screaming ]

771
01:11:02,961 --> 01:11:06,055
Call an ambulance !
Get an ambulance !

772
01:11:06,131 --> 01:11:09,191
Move it ! Move it !

773
01:11:09,267 --> 01:11:11,326
Get out of the way !
Move it !

774
01:11:12,404 --> 01:11:14,531
Excuse me.
Watch out ! Watch out !

775
01:11:14,606 --> 01:11:18,007
- Get out of the way !
- Watch out ! Watch out !

776
01:11:18,076 --> 01:11:20,704
- Move it ! Goddamn it, move !
- Move !

777
01:11:21,813 --> 01:11:24,509
Move it !
Get out of the way !

778
01:11:24,583 --> 01:11:28,212
Look out ! Look out !
Move ! Get out of the way !

779
01:11:32,057 --> 01:11:34,218
Get down ! Get down !

780
01:11:39,464 --> 01:11:42,729
[ Chattering In Japanese ]

781
01:12:14,712 --> 01:12:16,646
Goddamn it.

782
01:12:16,714 --> 01:12:20,309
[ Police Radio lndistinct ]

783
01:12:40,705 --> 01:12:44,869
Excuse me. F.B.l.
Where's your security office ?

784
01:12:44,943 --> 01:12:47,503
- Through the door to the right.
- Thank you.

785
01:12:56,621 --> 01:12:58,987
[ Knocks On Door ]

786
01:13:00,058 --> 01:13:01,992
[ Door Buzzes ]

787
01:13:02,060 --> 01:13:04,893
Hi. Special Agent Jeffries
with the F.B.l.

788
01:13:04,963 --> 01:13:07,591
- Can I help you ?
- I hope so.

789
01:13:09,167 --> 01:13:12,967
- Where's the tape for this camera ?
- Um, here it is.

790
01:13:24,983 --> 01:13:28,248
No, um... look,
it's my ass if you take that.

791
01:13:28,319 --> 01:13:31,550
Then don't tell anyone.
Thank you.

792
01:13:47,338 --> 01:13:50,034
Damn it.

793
01:14:03,388 --> 01:14:05,982
Excuse me,
excuse me please.

794
01:14:06,057 --> 01:14:07,991
Excuse me.
Whoa !

795
01:14:10,061 --> 01:14:13,087
Hey ! Come on.
We gotta go.

796
01:14:14,999 --> 01:14:17,024
- Sorry.
- What happened ?

797
01:14:17,101 --> 01:14:20,559
He almost got away. You didn't tell me
I have to watch him every second.

798
01:14:20,638 --> 01:14:23,072
Sorry. I shouldn't
have left the coffee shop.

799
01:14:23,141 --> 01:14:25,871
- No ! No !
- [ Tires Screeching ]

800
01:14:25,944 --> 01:14:27,878
- [ Simon Screaming ]
- All right, all right.

801
01:14:27,946 --> 01:14:31,609
Don't scream, don't scream.
All right.

802
01:14:33,318 --> 01:14:35,582
Oh, my God.

803
01:14:35,653 --> 01:14:38,087
He doesn't see things
like other people do.

804
01:14:47,699 --> 01:14:51,157
Where did you just go ?
Rob a bank or something ?

805
01:14:54,906 --> 01:14:57,340
I gotta get him out of here.
Let's go, Simon.

806
01:14:57,408 --> 01:15:01,902
Thank you, Stacey.
Thanks for all your help. Come on.

807
01:15:09,253 --> 01:15:11,312
# # [ Music Box ]

808
01:15:11,389 --> 01:15:14,187
- My dad will kill for this. How much ?
- One hundred.

809
01:15:14,258 --> 01:15:17,227
Get real.
Hey !

810
01:15:17,295 --> 01:15:20,731
Have you ever thought, what are
we gonna collect when we get old ?

811
01:15:20,798 --> 01:15:24,461
Plaid shirts
and Kramer dolls ?

812
01:15:24,535 --> 01:15:26,503
What's the matter ?

813
01:15:29,207 --> 01:15:32,540
- Dean is dead. He's been shot.
- What ?

814
01:15:34,012 --> 01:15:36,480
He wanted to go to Chicago.
I said, "Don't go."

815
01:15:36,547 --> 01:15:39,607
He wanted me to go with him
and help him.

816
01:15:39,684 --> 01:15:42,710
Someone shot him ?
Who would shoot him ?

817
01:15:42,787 --> 01:15:44,721
I can't tell you.

818
01:15:44,789 --> 01:15:48,316
Leo, I want to help you,
but you have to let me in.

819
01:15:48,393 --> 01:15:50,691
Tell me what's going on.

820
01:15:50,762 --> 01:15:54,391
- He'll find out.
- Who ? You mean Kudrow ?

821
01:15:54,465 --> 01:15:57,161
I don't have the capabilities
to E-mail over his head.

822
01:15:57,235 --> 01:15:59,567
I can't use the phone
because everything gets recorded.

823
01:15:59,637 --> 01:16:04,006
Everything is connected to everything.
There is nothing I can do.

824
01:16:15,286 --> 01:16:18,346
Low-tech rules.

825
01:16:25,530 --> 01:16:27,589
[ Tapping On Door ]

826
01:16:29,033 --> 01:16:31,331
[ Door Buzzes ]

827
01:16:43,448 --> 01:16:45,473
Congratulations.

828
01:16:45,550 --> 01:16:48,747
As of this morning, you made it
to the very top of our own perp board.

829
01:16:48,820 --> 01:16:51,653
I don't have to tell you
how profoundly pissed Lomax is.

830
01:16:51,722 --> 01:16:55,715
He's keeping a lid on it to cover
his ass, but you don't have much time.

831
01:16:55,793 --> 01:16:59,593
Yeah. Did you find out
who the shooter is ?

832
01:16:59,664 --> 01:17:03,327
Whatever happened to, "Good morning.
How are you ? Sorry about your car.

833
01:17:03,401 --> 01:17:06,859
It got impounded. You won't be able
to get it for two weeks."

834
01:17:06,938 --> 01:17:10,999
- Did you get in trouble ?
- No. I told them you stole it.

835
01:17:12,844 --> 01:17:15,244
Found him in the
Defense Department data banks.

836
01:17:15,313 --> 01:17:18,305
His name is Peter Burrell,
Special Forces.

837
01:17:19,717 --> 01:17:21,651
So, let's bring him in.

838
01:17:21,719 --> 01:17:25,587
Can't. Unless you want
to dig him up. He's dead.

839
01:17:25,656 --> 01:17:29,057
He's listed as killed
in Beirut in 1982.

840
01:17:33,064 --> 01:17:35,157
You still think
I'm paranoid ?

841
01:17:35,233 --> 01:17:37,793
I don't know, man.
Who knows ?

842
01:17:37,869 --> 01:17:41,032
But if you are, then I guess I'm
paranoid too. We're in over our heads.

843
01:17:41,105 --> 01:17:43,437
- We can't fuck with the N.S.A.
- So ?

844
01:17:43,508 --> 01:17:49,105
- We find somebody
to talk to about this.
- Lomax ? He's a Company man.

845
01:17:49,180 --> 01:17:51,944
- The N.S.A. could've gotten to him too.
- Fine. I'll go above Lomax.

846
01:17:52,016 --> 01:17:54,712
I don't want you
to do anything else.

847
01:17:54,785 --> 01:17:59,279
You got a wife and kid to take care of.
Go do that. Really.

848
01:17:59,357 --> 01:18:01,518
All right then.
What are you gonna do ?

849
01:18:03,461 --> 01:18:05,395
I don't know.

850
01:18:05,463 --> 01:18:08,364
[ Jordan ]
Why are you doing this, Art ?

851
01:18:08,432 --> 01:18:10,957
That kid isn't
your responsibility.

852
01:18:11,035 --> 01:18:13,868
Whose responsibility
is he ?

853
01:18:15,973 --> 01:18:19,431
Look at him.

854
01:18:19,510 --> 01:18:22,502
He looks like
a regular kid, right ?

855
01:18:22,580 --> 01:18:26,607
One little circuit
gets crossed. Zap !

856
01:18:26,684 --> 01:18:29,209
He should've been smart,
go to college,

857
01:18:29,287 --> 01:18:33,587
meet a girl, get married,
have some kids, be cool.

858
01:18:35,493 --> 01:18:38,929
Are we talking about him, Art,
or are we talking about you ?

859
01:18:44,769 --> 01:18:47,499
Thanks for getting this
together for me.

860
01:18:47,572 --> 01:18:49,870
Be careful.

861
01:18:49,941 --> 01:18:51,533
Yeah.

862
01:19:09,961 --> 01:19:12,794
- [ Door Closes ]
- Jesus !

863
01:19:12,863 --> 01:19:15,525
Who the fuck are you ?

864
01:19:15,600 --> 01:19:18,626
Oh. Oh.

865
01:19:18,703 --> 01:19:20,637
Please. Please--

866
01:19:20,705 --> 01:19:22,696
[ Gunshot ]

867
01:19:45,496 --> 01:19:47,623
[ Dog Barking ]

868
01:19:53,371 --> 01:19:55,771
[ Doorbell Buzzing ]

869
01:19:59,277 --> 01:20:03,077
[ Buzzing Continues ]

870
01:20:05,716 --> 01:20:09,618
Okay ! Oh. You.
What do you want ?

871
01:20:09,687 --> 01:20:14,750
[ Sighs ] It's 2:00 in the morning,
and you don't know me this well.

872
01:20:14,825 --> 01:20:18,591
- I need to talk to you.
- You're gonna wake up my neighbors.

873
01:20:20,964 --> 01:20:27,271
[ Sighs ]
Oh, man.

874
01:20:27,271 --> 01:20:29,501
We need a place to stay.

875
01:20:29,573 --> 01:20:32,565
- How'd you get this address ?
- I looked it up.

876
01:20:32,643 --> 01:20:34,838
No, it's not listed.

877
01:20:34,912 --> 01:20:39,246
The name of your company was on the side
of your sample case. I called them.

878
01:20:39,316 --> 01:20:43,776
Right. Call my company, ask 'em
for my address, they give it to you ?

879
01:20:43,854 --> 01:20:45,549
Nope.

880
01:20:45,622 --> 01:20:50,059
Please. Stacey.

881
01:20:50,127 --> 01:20:52,960
[ Sighs ]
I'm an F.B.l. agent.

882
01:20:53,030 --> 01:20:56,466
Yeah. I bought one of those
for my little brother, $5.

883
01:20:56,533 --> 01:20:59,934
I saw you hiding from the police today.
I'll give them a call.

884
01:21:00,003 --> 01:21:04,099
Listen.
I really am an F.B.l agent.

885
01:21:04,174 --> 01:21:07,234
Please help us.

886
01:21:07,311 --> 01:21:11,270
- Hello, Simon.
- Hello.

887
01:21:12,883 --> 01:21:14,817
Please.

888
01:21:14,885 --> 01:21:17,046
Move your foot.

889
01:21:29,566 --> 01:21:31,261
Thank you.

890
01:21:34,371 --> 01:21:37,101
Thank you very much.

891
01:21:37,174 --> 01:21:41,736
Would it be stupid to ask
why you don't call the F.B.l. for help ?

892
01:21:41,812 --> 01:21:43,905
The F.B.l.'s
looking for me too.

893
01:21:43,981 --> 01:21:45,676
Oh, great.

894
01:21:45,749 --> 01:21:50,152
So, how does this work ? You murder me
now or you wait till I'm asleep ?

895
01:21:52,723 --> 01:21:55,157
Simon needs to get
a little sleep.

896
01:21:55,225 --> 01:22:00,060
He's been up for a long time,
and you seemed like a nice person.

897
01:22:01,365 --> 01:22:06,735
Come on, Simon.
I'll show you where your bed is.

898
01:22:06,804 --> 01:22:09,102
Come on.

899
01:22:09,173 --> 01:22:11,869
Are you thirsty ?

900
01:22:11,942 --> 01:22:15,105
He gets the guest room.
You get the couch.

901
01:22:15,179 --> 01:22:17,306
There's food in there.

902
01:22:17,381 --> 01:22:21,010
The bathroom.
You can wash up after yourself.

903
01:22:27,024 --> 01:22:29,185
[ Stacey ]
Let's take this off.

904
01:22:31,662 --> 01:22:34,893
That's good.
Now lie down.

905
01:22:38,435 --> 01:22:41,029
Okay ?

906
01:22:41,104 --> 01:22:43,698
Let's take these off,
all right ?

907
01:22:43,774 --> 01:22:47,471
One. Two.

908
01:22:47,544 --> 01:22:50,411
[ Stacey ]
Okay.

909
01:22:50,480 --> 01:22:52,710
That's good.

910
01:22:55,285 --> 01:22:57,583
You okay ?

911
01:22:57,654 --> 01:22:59,622
Good night, Simon.

912
01:23:01,725 --> 01:23:03,454
Look,

913
01:23:03,527 --> 01:23:06,655
I have to be up
in a few hours.

914
01:23:06,730 --> 01:23:09,528
I have to fly to Des Moines
in the morning.

915
01:23:09,600 --> 01:23:14,230
If I don't make a sale there tomorrow,
then I don't pay my rent.

916
01:23:14,304 --> 01:23:18,400
So, unless there's anything else you
need, I'd like to get some sleep now.

917
01:23:18,475 --> 01:23:22,172
No, there's nothing else.
Thank you.

918
01:23:22,246 --> 01:23:26,273
I promise you we'll be out of here
first thing in the morning.

919
01:23:34,157 --> 01:23:36,648
[ Bicycle Bell Rings ]

920
01:24:00,217 --> 01:24:04,176
Leo, you won't believe the morning.
Did I leave my--

921
01:24:04,254 --> 01:24:06,449
Leo ?

922
01:24:09,860 --> 01:24:12,226
[ Gasps ]

923
01:24:12,296 --> 01:24:14,764
Oh, my God !

924
01:24:23,640 --> 01:24:26,074
[ Phone Ringing ]

925
01:24:27,844 --> 01:24:31,507
Tom, there's a woman downstairs
asking to see Art Jeffries.

926
01:24:31,581 --> 01:24:35,347
- Bring her up.
- She won't talk to anyone except Art.

927
01:24:35,419 --> 01:24:37,410
Do me a favor.

928
01:24:37,487 --> 01:24:40,285
I haven't
logged it in... yet.

929
01:24:40,357 --> 01:24:42,291
Good.

930
01:24:50,233 --> 01:24:52,701
[ Tapping On Door ]

931
01:25:01,678 --> 01:25:04,841
[ Door Buzzes ]

932
01:25:14,124 --> 01:25:17,457
- How ya doin', man ?
- Anybody else with you ?

933
01:25:17,527 --> 01:25:20,052
No.

934
01:25:20,130 --> 01:25:22,690
This is Emily Lang.

935
01:25:22,766 --> 01:25:25,929
Emily, why don't you have a seat ?
Go ahead.

936
01:25:33,143 --> 01:25:35,168
Are you Art Jeffries ?

937
01:25:35,245 --> 01:25:37,770
Yeah,
I'm Art Jeffries.

938
01:25:45,922 --> 01:25:49,221
My boyfriend's last will
and testament.

939
01:25:49,292 --> 01:25:51,783
I worked with him
at N.S.A.

940
01:25:53,096 --> 01:25:55,929
The other voice
on the line.

941
01:25:55,999 --> 01:25:59,025
His name was Leo.

942
01:25:59,102 --> 01:26:01,536
He was gonna mail one letter
to you.

943
01:26:01,605 --> 01:26:05,200
The other was addressed to
the Senate Oversight Committee.

944
01:26:05,275 --> 01:26:07,368
The letters are gone.
This is all that's left.

945
01:26:07,444 --> 01:26:09,674
"lt has come
to my attention...

946
01:26:09,746 --> 01:26:13,910
"that my section director and
immediate superior, Nicholas Kudrow,

947
01:26:13,984 --> 01:26:18,114
"was directly involved in
the deaths of Martin and Jenny Lynch,

948
01:26:20,190 --> 01:26:22,488
"the parents
of Simon Lynch,

949
01:26:22,559 --> 01:26:25,790
and the death of Dean Crandell,
my colleague and friend."

950
01:26:25,862 --> 01:26:30,356
They killed Leo too right after
he wrote that letter.

951
01:26:30,434 --> 01:26:33,699
[ Crying ]
I'm sorry.

952
01:26:33,770 --> 01:26:35,761
I'm sorry.

953
01:26:40,544 --> 01:26:43,638
Thank you for coming down,
Emily.

954
01:26:43,713 --> 01:26:46,580
I'm sorry about Leo.

955
01:26:46,650 --> 01:26:49,050
You said you were gonna be out before
I went to Des Moines...

956
01:26:49,119 --> 01:26:51,519
where hopefully I was gonna sell
enough shoes to make the rent.

957
01:26:51,588 --> 01:26:55,285
Only I didn't go to Des Moines
and I didn't make the rent
because you had an emergency.

958
01:26:55,358 --> 01:26:57,326
[ Art ]
It was an emergency.

959
01:26:57,394 --> 01:26:59,885
Maybe you're one of those guys
that has constant emergencies.

960
01:26:59,963 --> 01:27:03,956
Everything has to be about excitement.
There are guys like that.

961
01:27:04,034 --> 01:27:07,936
Y es, I know, but I don't happen
to be one of them.

962
01:27:08,004 --> 01:27:12,338
Listen to me. Look at me !
This is not about me.

963
01:27:12,409 --> 01:27:15,344
It's about that little boy.
And he needs some help.

964
01:27:15,412 --> 01:27:18,279
As far as I can tell,
you are a decent, caring person.

965
01:27:18,348 --> 01:27:23,149
I promise you we will be out
of your life as soon as possible. Okay ?

966
01:27:23,220 --> 01:27:26,189
Look, if for some reason
there is an emergency--

967
01:27:26,256 --> 01:27:29,225
- Oh ! You mean a different emergency !
- Yes, a different emergency.

968
01:27:29,292 --> 01:27:33,592
Do not call the police, okay ?
You call this guy. He's with the F.B.l.

969
01:27:33,663 --> 01:27:36,723
I call the F.B.l.,
not the police ?

970
01:27:36,800 --> 01:27:39,860
- Right. The police can't protect Simon.
- Right.

971
01:27:39,936 --> 01:27:42,427
Look.

972
01:27:42,506 --> 01:27:45,873
Simon is only in danger
if they know where he is.

973
01:27:45,942 --> 01:27:51,209
They don't know where he is,
so he's not in danger, so you're
not in danger. All right ?

974
01:27:51,281 --> 01:27:54,648
Right. Unless
there's an emergency.

975
01:27:54,718 --> 01:27:56,310
[ Chuckles ]

976
01:27:56,386 --> 01:28:01,824
- It's good to see you're keeping
your sense of humor about this.
- Yeah.

977
01:28:01,892 --> 01:28:07,091
I promise you I will be back in this
apartment at 2:00 tomorrow afternoon.

978
01:28:07,164 --> 01:28:11,430
And I don't know how yet,
but I will make this up to you.

979
01:28:11,501 --> 01:28:13,662
Okay ?
Thank you.

980
01:28:13,737 --> 01:28:16,716
Take care.

981
01:28:18,585 --> 01:28:21,418
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

982
01:28:28,027 --> 01:28:32,555
I don't know if it qualifies
as a plan. I'm gonna fly there
and show them Leo's letter.

983
01:28:32,632 --> 01:28:35,726
Here's the bad news.

984
01:28:35,802 --> 01:28:39,294
You gotta get Simon into the
Witness Protection Program right away.

985
01:28:39,372 --> 01:28:42,637
Art, I'm not even supposed
to be talking to you.

986
01:28:42,709 --> 01:28:45,803
How do you expect me to authorize
a move like that ?

987
01:28:45,878 --> 01:28:50,747
Lie, cheat. I don't give a shit. You
don't do it, that kid's as good as dead.

988
01:28:50,817 --> 01:28:54,309
Has it occurred to you that maybe Kudrow
would shoot you on sight ?

989
01:28:54,387 --> 01:28:56,878
Y eah, that has occurred
to me.

990
01:28:56,956 --> 01:29:00,483
If that happens,
you know what to do with these.

991
01:29:00,560 --> 01:29:03,757
Hope I see you later.

992
01:29:12,905 --> 01:29:15,271
Sandy !
So glad you could make it.

993
01:29:15,341 --> 01:29:20,142
Heard Ted had back surgery. Did you have
anything to do with that ? Excuse me.

994
01:29:28,021 --> 01:29:29,955
Can I help you ?

995
01:29:31,057 --> 01:29:33,491
Excuse me.
Nick, my good friend !

996
01:29:33,559 --> 01:29:37,655
I want you to know that
your Mercury thing is a goddamn triumph.

997
01:29:37,730 --> 01:29:40,028
- I mean that.
- I appreciate that, Senator.

998
01:29:40,099 --> 01:29:44,092
A feather in your cap. The Oversight
Committee is singing your praises.

999
01:29:44,170 --> 01:29:46,661
You're getting a reputation
as the "can do" guy.

1000
01:29:46,739 --> 01:29:49,674
- Thank you. I do appreciate that.
- There's a guy outside.

1001
01:29:49,742 --> 01:29:51,676
- Who ?
- Says he's with the Bureau.

1002
01:29:51,744 --> 01:29:54,645
Would you excuse me
one moment, please ?

1003
01:29:56,449 --> 01:29:59,475
If he wasn't Bureau,
I wouldn't have bothered you.

1004
01:29:59,552 --> 01:30:01,918
I would've lost him,
but I didn't know, sir.

1005
01:30:01,988 --> 01:30:04,980
No, Ted, you used good judgment.
I'd like to see him.

1006
01:30:05,058 --> 01:30:06,992
He's not
very presentable.

1007
01:30:07,060 --> 01:30:10,393
Bring him in the back way. Take him
to the wine cellar. I'll be down.

1008
01:30:13,533 --> 01:30:16,832
Nick, I can't believe you look so good
for someone so old !

1009
01:30:16,903 --> 01:30:20,600
-How do you do that ?
-Drugs, my dear. Massive doses of drugs.

1010
01:30:20,673 --> 01:30:24,871
[ Kudrow ] Please don't handle
the wine, Mr. Jeffries.

1011
01:30:24,944 --> 01:30:28,436
Yes, I've read
your file.

1012
01:30:30,350 --> 01:30:33,183
A deeply troubled F.B.l. agent
with a lousy record...

1013
01:30:33,252 --> 01:30:35,243
kidnaps
a nine-year-old boy.

1014
01:30:35,321 --> 01:30:37,346
Nice goin'.

1015
01:30:37,423 --> 01:30:42,087
You come to my home in the middle
of a social function carrying a gun...

1016
01:30:42,161 --> 01:30:45,722
to confront me with this fabricated
unsigned accusation,

1017
01:30:45,798 --> 01:30:47,789
allegedly written
by Leo Pedranski...

1018
01:30:47,867 --> 01:30:51,462
who was killed the day before yesterday
by you, for all I know.

1019
01:30:51,537 --> 01:30:55,371
What do you want from me ?
I'd like to get back to my guests.

1020
01:30:55,441 --> 01:31:00,140
Unsigned accusation
was typed on carbon paper.

1021
01:31:00,213 --> 01:31:02,374
Who uses that anymore ?

1022
01:31:02,448 --> 01:31:05,679
The late Leo Pedranski's
fingerprints were all over it.

1023
01:31:08,020 --> 01:31:10,580
The Pomerello's
a little corky.

1024
01:31:10,656 --> 01:31:14,956
I'm sure the Senate Oversight
Committee won't have any problem
connecting you to the murder.

1025
01:31:15,027 --> 01:31:19,964
But you haven't given the carbon
to the Senate Oversight Committee.

1026
01:31:20,032 --> 01:31:23,092
If you had, you wouldn't
be here right now.

1027
01:31:23,169 --> 01:31:26,104
You've got your precious
carbon tucked away...

1028
01:31:26,172 --> 01:31:28,697
guaranteeing your safety,
etcetera, etcetera...

1029
01:31:28,775 --> 01:31:30,709
so you can come here
and demand what ?

1030
01:31:30,810 --> 01:31:33,973
Untold millions
in unmarked bills ?

1031
01:31:34,046 --> 01:31:37,345
- I asked you
not to handle the wine, please.
- [ Laughing ]

1032
01:31:37,417 --> 01:31:41,649
You know, it's good to see you got
your priorities in order.

1033
01:31:43,723 --> 01:31:45,657
That's better.

1034
01:31:45,725 --> 01:31:48,660
You're not worried about
murdering a nine-year-old boy,

1035
01:31:48,728 --> 01:31:50,787
but you're worried about
this fucking wine ?

1036
01:31:50,863 --> 01:31:54,594
- [ Glass Shattering ]
- Here's the deal.

1037
01:31:54,667 --> 01:31:57,830
I don't give the Senate
Oversight Committee the carbon.

1038
01:31:57,904 --> 01:32:01,271
They don't waste three years with their
investigation, wailing and moaning,

1039
01:32:01,340 --> 01:32:03,672
"How could this happen
in America ?"...

1040
01:32:03,743 --> 01:32:06,678
while you have one of
your spooks whack Simon Lynch.

1041
01:32:06,746 --> 01:32:08,941
Or ?

1042
01:32:09,015 --> 01:32:12,451
Or you do the only thing that'll
guarantee Simon Lynch his safety.

1043
01:32:12,518 --> 01:32:16,318
You or one of your superiors or
the president of the United States,

1044
01:32:16,389 --> 01:32:18,482
I don't give a fuck who,

1045
01:32:18,558 --> 01:32:21,322
but someone is gonna go on
national television and tell America...

1046
01:32:21,394 --> 01:32:24,522
that your billion dollar,
uncrackable code...

1047
01:32:24,597 --> 01:32:27,395
has been cracked by
a nine-year-old autistic boy.

1048
01:32:27,467 --> 01:32:29,526
Then you get
your carbon back.

1049
01:32:34,907 --> 01:32:38,172
You know what I think,
Mr. Jeffries ?

1050
01:32:38,244 --> 01:32:42,840
I think you've seen too many of those
four-wheel drive commercials on TV.

1051
01:32:42,915 --> 01:32:45,042
[ Laughing ]

1052
01:32:45,117 --> 01:32:47,915
The ones where you get to drive fast
and be a renegade.

1053
01:32:47,987 --> 01:32:50,820
Let's talk about
the real world...

1054
01:32:50,890 --> 01:32:55,486
where you're not some wonderful lone
wolf hero, but you're part of a team.

1055
01:32:55,561 --> 01:32:59,622
And you play your position
because that's what America is.

1056
01:32:59,699 --> 01:33:02,429
It's one big team.

1057
01:33:02,502 --> 01:33:07,838
This might be difficult
for you to grasp, but I am a patriot.

1058
01:33:07,907 --> 01:33:12,105
And a patriot is one who makes
the right moral choice.

1059
01:33:12,178 --> 01:33:15,841
Sometimes it takes a strong man
to make that choice.

1060
01:33:15,915 --> 01:33:21,012
One boy who cannot survive on his own,
one of nature's mistakes,

1061
01:33:21,087 --> 01:33:24,488
weighed against the lives
of thousands of our people.

1062
01:33:24,557 --> 01:33:27,151
Think about it.
You worked undercover.

1063
01:33:27,226 --> 01:33:30,923
How many of our agents will
be put in harm's way
if this code is compromised ?

1064
01:33:30,997 --> 01:33:33,090
Members of your team.

1065
01:33:33,165 --> 01:33:35,861
Men like Rasheed Halabi,

1066
01:33:35,935 --> 01:33:39,268
an lraqi-American
and a great patriot.

1067
01:33:39,338 --> 01:33:43,274
A man, who as we speak, is undercover
in Saddam's Republican Guard.

1068
01:33:43,342 --> 01:33:46,368
A man who has not seen
his family--

1069
01:33:48,514 --> 01:33:51,608
That's for Simon's parents,
you piece of shit.

1070
01:33:51,684 --> 01:33:53,311
[ Coughing ]

1071
01:33:53,386 --> 01:33:55,377
You got 36 hours.

1072
01:33:55,454 --> 01:33:59,390
Should be enough time to get your
undercover people out of harm's way.

1073
01:34:02,194 --> 01:34:06,255
Oh, by the way.
Happy birthday, Nick.

1074
01:34:11,537 --> 01:34:15,200
[ Phone Ringing ]

1075
01:34:18,377 --> 01:34:21,835
- Hello ?
- [ Art ] Hey, it's me.

1076
01:34:22,915 --> 01:34:24,849
Y eah.
You all right ?

1077
01:34:24,917 --> 01:34:28,114
Y eah, I'm all right. How'd it go
with the witness protection thing ?

1078
01:34:28,187 --> 01:34:31,213
[ Jordan ] Everything's set.
Tomorrow night, 8::15,

1079
01:34:31,290 --> 01:34:33,281
U.S. marshalls are gonna meet us
with a chopper...

1080
01:34:33,359 --> 01:34:36,328
at the heliport on top
of the G.E.X. building.

1081
01:34:36,395 --> 01:34:38,454
I took your advice.
I lied.

1082
01:34:38,531 --> 01:34:41,796
[ Art ] All right. Good.
See you then. Bye.

1083
01:34:41,867 --> 01:34:43,801
[ Phone Disconnects ]

1084
01:34:43,869 --> 01:34:46,429
That was recorded
on passive V.O.X...

1085
01:34:46,505 --> 01:34:49,633
at Agent Jordan's
residence at 11:58 p.m.

1086
01:34:49,709 --> 01:34:52,701
As to the pickup, since we can assume
the boy will not be alone,

1087
01:34:52,778 --> 01:34:56,839
I suggest we wait until
we get him on the chopper.

1088
01:34:56,916 --> 01:34:59,544
- [ TV ] Saw them do this in the movies.
- [ Phone Ringing ]

1089
01:35:01,854 --> 01:35:04,721
How are you, laddie boy ?

1090
01:35:04,790 --> 01:35:08,521
- [ Shower Water Running ]
- [ Phone Ringing ]

1091
01:35:11,664 --> 01:35:13,723
Oh, damn !

1092
01:35:13,799 --> 01:35:17,326
- Simon, turn it down, please !
- [ Ringing Continues ]

1093
01:35:17,403 --> 01:35:19,530
Hello ?

1094
01:35:19,605 --> 01:35:21,835
Hello ?

1095
01:35:22,908 --> 01:35:25,376
Hello ?

1096
01:35:25,444 --> 01:35:27,674
[ Dial Tone ]

1097
01:35:35,488 --> 01:35:37,479
How much I owe you ?

1098
01:35:37,556 --> 01:35:40,081
- Twenty dollars, sir.
- Here. Thanks a lot.

1099
01:35:48,467 --> 01:35:50,401
Stacey ?

1100
01:35:53,439 --> 01:35:55,532
Stacey ?

1101
01:36:00,079 --> 01:36:02,070
Shit !

1102
01:36:09,522 --> 01:36:12,218
[ Phone Ringing ]

1103
01:36:12,291 --> 01:36:14,934
- Hello ?
- Tommy, where are they now ?

1104
01:36:14,934 --> 01:36:16,799
- Hello ?
- Tommy, where are they now ?

1105
01:36:16,869 --> 01:36:19,337
Relax. Simon and the girl
are fine. I talked to 'em.

1106
01:36:19,405 --> 01:36:21,396
She said she got spooked.
Someone called.

1107
01:36:21,473 --> 01:36:25,876
- When she picked up the phone
the line was dead.
- It was me from the airplane.

1108
01:36:25,945 --> 01:36:30,473
- Told 'em when Witness Protection
is gonna pick 'em up ?
- Absolutely.

1109
01:36:30,549 --> 01:36:32,949
She's gonna meet us there.
Everything's set.

1110
01:36:33,018 --> 01:36:35,646
[ Jordan ]
Listen, I gotta go.

1111
01:36:39,124 --> 01:36:41,092
[ Lomax ]
Agent Jordan.

1112
01:36:41,160 --> 01:36:45,221
Lieutenant Colonel Kudrow
of the N.S.A.

1113
01:36:45,297 --> 01:36:47,857
What am I looking at here,
Tommy ?

1114
01:36:47,933 --> 01:36:51,266
You forged documents to obtain witness
protection under false pretenses.

1115
01:36:51,337 --> 01:36:56,707
Don't listen to anything this guy
tells you. This guy is dangerous.

1116
01:36:56,775 --> 01:36:58,868
Tommy, sit down,
and don't speak.

1117
01:37:06,919 --> 01:37:09,353
Agent Jordan,

1118
01:37:09,421 --> 01:37:11,889
regardless of what
you think of me,

1119
01:37:11,957 --> 01:37:14,926
I only want to resolve
this situation to rescue a young boy...

1120
01:37:14,994 --> 01:37:17,554
from a delusional kidnapper.

1121
01:37:17,629 --> 01:37:20,359
We will proceed
with the pickup as planned.

1122
01:37:20,432 --> 01:37:23,299
As of this moment,
the F.B.l. will stand down...

1123
01:37:23,369 --> 01:37:26,896
and the N.S.A.
will take over from here.

1124
01:37:26,972 --> 01:37:29,133
Gentlemen.

1125
01:37:32,678 --> 01:37:36,739
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

1126
01:37:36,815 --> 01:37:39,340
- Chief, take a look at this.
- I'm not taking a look.

1127
01:37:39,418 --> 01:37:44,412
You have to look at this ! Leo Pedranski
worked for Kudrow. He wrote that letter.

1128
01:37:44,490 --> 01:37:46,856
He was also killed
after he wrote it.

1129
01:37:46,925 --> 01:37:50,361
I ran it through the lab.
And the fingerprints on it
are an exact match for his.

1130
01:38:01,340 --> 01:38:03,331
[ Simon ]
Up.

1131
01:38:03,409 --> 01:38:06,378
That's where we're goin',
Simon.

1132
01:38:08,614 --> 01:38:10,548
Come on.

1133
01:38:12,985 --> 01:38:16,079
[ Elevator Bell Rings ]

1134
01:38:25,230 --> 01:38:27,164
[ Elevator Bell Rings ]

1135
01:38:37,876 --> 01:38:40,709
[ Stacey ]
Is that you, Art ?

1136
01:38:43,215 --> 01:38:46,776
I'm a United States marshall
with the Witness Protection Program.

1137
01:38:47,986 --> 01:38:50,921
How do you do ?

1138
01:38:50,989 --> 01:38:53,321
Good.

1139
01:38:56,128 --> 01:38:58,119
You must be Simon.

1140
01:38:58,197 --> 01:39:01,064
[ Burrell ]
Chopper on approach, sir.

1141
01:39:01,133 --> 01:39:03,693
Why don't you come
with me, son ?

1142
01:39:03,769 --> 01:39:06,363
- No !
- He doesn't like
to be touched by strangers.

1143
01:39:06,438 --> 01:39:09,532
I'll take him.

1144
01:39:09,608 --> 01:39:13,044
Come on, Simon.
Let's go see the helicopter.

1145
01:39:15,180 --> 01:39:18,877
- I thought Art was supposed
to meet us here.
- There's been a change in plans.

1146
01:39:18,951 --> 01:39:22,352
But I want to assure you
that your country owes you
the greatest debt of gratitude.

1147
01:39:22,421 --> 01:39:25,822
[ Burrell ] Chopper coming in !
Don't have much time !

1148
01:39:27,726 --> 01:39:31,628
For the safety of the boy, you should
go home now and forget you were here.

1149
01:39:34,733 --> 01:39:38,191
Okay, Simon, you're gonna go for a ride
in the helicopter.

1150
01:39:38,270 --> 01:39:40,204
Good-bye, Simon.

1151
01:39:42,274 --> 01:39:44,367
You can go with him.

1152
01:40:05,097 --> 01:40:07,031
Tommy.

1153
01:40:07,099 --> 01:40:09,727
[ Lomax ] They're on the helipad,
and the chopper's coming in.

1154
01:40:09,801 --> 01:40:11,735
You have a green light.
Go, go, go, go !

1155
01:40:11,803 --> 01:40:13,668
- It's a go. Let's move.
- Go, go !

1156
01:40:17,776 --> 01:40:19,403
Hold them back !

1157
01:40:25,984 --> 01:40:28,475
Stay down !
Stay down !

1158
01:40:38,697 --> 01:40:42,258
[ Screaming ]
No ! No !

1159
01:40:45,370 --> 01:40:48,100
[ Screaming ]
No !

1160
01:40:59,651 --> 01:41:01,881
[ Grunts ]

1161
01:41:08,427 --> 01:41:10,361
[ Gunshots Continue ]

1162
01:41:19,071 --> 01:41:21,062
No ! No ! Simon !

1163
01:41:44,763 --> 01:41:48,290
- [ Kudrow Screams ]
- [ Art ] Let me go. Come on !

1164
01:41:48,367 --> 01:41:53,031
No ! No !
No, Simon, no !

1165
01:42:16,128 --> 01:42:17,618
[ Gasps ]

1166
01:42:17,696 --> 01:42:20,893
Get up. Get up, get up.

1167
01:42:20,966 --> 01:42:23,127
That's right.

1168
01:42:50,629 --> 01:42:53,393
- Tommy, no ! Hold 'em back !
- [ Jordan ] Hold your fire !

1169
01:42:53,465 --> 01:42:56,866
- Keep 'em back now !
- [ Simon Screaming ]

1170
01:42:58,003 --> 01:43:01,234
[ Simon Screaming ]
No !

1171
01:43:33,605 --> 01:43:35,539
Where's the team leader ?

1172
01:43:35,607 --> 01:43:40,408
- Right here, Agent Jeffries.
- It's Kudrow's piece. I got a
nine-millimeter on the sidewalk.

1173
01:43:40,479 --> 01:43:42,413
I'll take care of it.

1174
01:44:19,240 --> 01:44:24,143
[ Teacher ]
Let's see what you got.

1175
01:44:24,212 --> 01:44:26,237
- I want you to say "bug."
- [ Girl ] Bug.

1176
01:44:26,314 --> 01:44:30,307
Can you look at me ?
Bug.

1177
01:44:30,385 --> 01:44:32,376
- Bug.
- That's very good.

1178
01:44:32,453 --> 01:44:34,648
[ Teacher ]
I like that very much.

1179
01:44:41,229 --> 01:44:43,220
Can I help you ?

1180
01:44:43,298 --> 01:44:46,563
I'm Art Jeffries,
a friend of Simon Lynch.

1181
01:44:46,634 --> 01:44:50,695
Yes, I know. His foster parents
told me all about you.

1182
01:44:50,772 --> 01:44:52,706
How's he doing ?

1183
01:44:52,774 --> 01:44:57,177
He's fine.
He's adjusted very well.

1184
01:44:58,246 --> 01:45:00,305
Do you want
to say hello ?

1185
01:45:00,381 --> 01:45:03,441
He probably wouldn't
remember me.

1186
